Encountering the Sources of the Classic of Materia Medica notes that although Eriobotryae Folium (æ‡æ·è‘‰ pi pa ye) is commonly used for cough, nausea, and vomiting, "it is still contraindicated for nausea and vomiting from Stomach cold, or cough due to wind-cold." These conditions can still be treated with this herb, however, if the leaves are prepared with ginger, and other appropriate herbs are added.
Use with caution for cough or vomiting due to cold.

